               <msContents>
                  <summary>Fragment of a geography of the Aeolian Islands (col. I) and of Sicily (col. II), mentioning also Kyme in Campania (Italy); it combined mythological geography (in part. the geography of the Odyssey) and an interest for natural (volcanic) phenomena, and gave distance figures betweenplaces</summary>
