                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The professional character of the writing together with the evenness of the lines and the seeming absence of spelling mistakes are evidence of a painstaking, experienced scribe. Small, rather formal book hand, employing decorative finials on a number of latters. Punctuation (high stops in I, 5; II, 14; paragraphi (II, 3-4; 9-10; 20-21). (Renner)</p>
